4 dead in Swiss helicopter crash
Multimedia   ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures Send us your pictures  ·  Send us your stories
Berlin - Four men including the 62-year-old pilot have died in a helicopter crash in southern Switzerland.
Police in the Italian-speaking canton (state) of Ticino said the helicopter with six people on board crashed after clipping a boulder as it was taking off from a granite quarry near the town of Lodrino early on Saturday.
Local news portal Ticino Online reported that they managed to jump out of the helicopter before it hit the ground.